    <h1>Installation</h1>
    <p class="subtitle">Multiple ways to install KCode on Linux, macOS, and Windows (WSL).</p>

    <h2>One-Line Install (Recommended)</h2>
    <p>The quickest way to get started. Downloads the latest release and adds <code>kcode</code> to your PATH:</p>
    <pre><code>curl -fsSL https://kulvex.ai/install.sh | bash</code></pre>
    <p>The installer auto-detects your OS and architecture (x86_64, aarch64) and places the binary in <code>~/.local/bin/kcode</code>.</p>

    <h2>Homebrew (macOS / Linux)</h2>
    <pre><code>brew install astrolexis/tap/kcode</code></pre>
    <p>Updates are handled automatically via <code>brew upgrade kcode</code>.</p>

    <h2>npm</h2>
    <pre><code>npm install -g kcode</code></pre>
    <p>Requires Node.js 18+ or Bun. The npm package bundles the Bun runtime so no extra dependencies are needed.</p>

    <h2>Bun (Native)</h2>
    <p>Since KCode is built with Bun, you can install directly:</p>
    <pre><code>bun install -g kcode</code></pre>
    <p>Or run without installing:</p>
    <pre><code>bunx kcode "your prompt here"</code></pre>

    <h2>From Source</h2>
    <p>Clone the repository and build locally. Requires <a href="https://bun.sh">Bun</a> v1.1+.</p>
    <pre><code># Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/astrolexis/kcode.git
cd kcode

# Install dependencies
bun install

# Run directly (no build needed, 0 MB overhead)
bun run src/index.ts

# Or create a production build (~101 MB, minified)
bun run build
./dist/kcode</code></pre>

    <h2>Verify Installation</h2>
    <p>After installing, verify everything is working:</p>
    <pre><code># Check version
kcode --version

# Run the environment diagnostic
kcode doctor</code></pre>
    <p>The <code>kcode doctor</code> command checks your system for:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Bun / Node.js runtime availability</li>
      <li>GPU detection (CUDA, ROCm, Metal)</li>
      <li>Available disk space for model storage</li>
      <li>Network connectivity to API providers</li>
      <li>Local inference server status (llama.cpp / Ollama)</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Shell Completions</h2>
    <p>Generate tab completions for your shell:</p>
    <pre><code># Bash
kcode completions bash >> ~/.bashrc

# Zsh
kcode completions zsh >> ~/.zshrc

# Fish
kcode completions fish > ~/.config/fish/completions/kcode.fish</code></pre>

    <h2>Updating</h2>
    <p>KCode checks for updates automatically every 7 days (configurable). To update manually:</p>
    <pre><code># Check for updates
kcode update

# Or via your package manager
brew upgrade kcode
npm update -g kcode</code></pre>
    <p>Auto-update checks can be disabled in your settings:</p>
    <pre><code>{
  "autoUpdate": false
}</code></pre>

    <h2>Uninstalling</h2>
    <pre><code># Remove the binary
rm ~/.local/bin/kcode

# Remove configuration and data (optional)
rm -rf ~/.kcode

# Or via package manager
brew uninstall kcode
npm uninstall -g kcode</code></pre>

    <h2>System Requirements</h2>
    <table>
      <thead><tr><th>Component</th><th>Minimum</th><th>Recommended</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>OS</td><td>Linux, macOS 12+, Windows (WSL2)</td><td>Linux with NVIDIA GPU</td></tr>
        <tr><td>RAM</td><td>4 GB</td><td>16 GB+ (for local models)</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Disk</td><td>200 MB (binary)</td><td>10 GB+ (with local models)</td></tr>
        <tr><td>GPU (optional)</td><td>4 GB VRAM</td><td>8 GB+ VRAM (CUDA or ROCm)</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Runtime</td><td>Bun 1.1+ or Node.js 18+</td><td>Bun 1.1+</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

